     {"element":
      ["p",
       true,
       [],
       [{"text": "The input "},
        {"element": ["code", true, [], [{"text": "e"}]]},
        {"text": " in "},
        {"element":
         ["code",
          true,
          [],
          [{"text": "linear_combination"}, {"text": " "}, {"text": "e"}]]},
        {"text": " is a linear combination of proofs of (in)equalities,"},
        {"raw": "\n"},
        {"text":
         "given as a sum/difference of coefficients multiplied by expressions."},
        {"raw": "\n"},
        {"text":
         "The coefficients may be arbitrary expressions (with nonnegativity constraints in the case of"},
        {"raw": "\n"},
        {"text": "inequalities)."},
        {"raw": "\n"},
        {"text":
         "The expressions can be arbitrary proof terms proving (in)equalities;"},
        {"raw": "\n"},
        {"text": "most commonly they are hypothesis names "},
        {"element": ["code", true, [], [{"text": "h1"}]]},
        {"text": ", "},
        {"element": ["code", true, [], [{"text": "h2"}]]},
        {"text": ", ...."}]]},
     {"element":
      ["p",
       true,
       [],
       [{"text":
         "The left and right sides of all the (in)equalities should have the same type "},
        {"element": ["code", true, [], [{"text": "α"}]]},
        {"text": ", and the"},
        {"raw": "\n"},
        {"text": "coefficients should also have type "},
        {"element": ["code", true, [], [{"text": "α"}]]},
        {"text": ".  For full functionality "},
        {"element": ["code", true, [], [{"text": "α"}]]},
        {"text": " should be a commutative ring --"},
        {"raw": "\n"},
        {"text":
         "strictly speaking, a commutative semiring with \"cancellative\" addition (in the semiring case,"},
        {"raw": "\n"},
        {"text":
         "negation and subtraction will be handled \"formally\" as if operating in the enveloping ring). If a"},
        {"raw": "\n"},
        {"text": "nonstandard normalization is used (for example "},
        {"element": ["code", true, [], [{"text": "abel"}]]},
        {"text": " or "},
        {"element": ["code", true, [], [{"text": "skip"}]]},
        {"text": "), the tactic will work over types"},
        {"raw": "\n"},
        {"element": ["code", true, [], [{"text": "α"}]]},
        {"text":
         " with less algebraic structure: for equalities, the minimum is instances of"},
        {"raw": "\n"},
        {"element":
         ["code",
          true,
          [],
          [{"text": "[Add"},
           {"text": " "},
           {"text": "α]"},
           {"text": " "},
           {"text": "[IsRightCancelAdd"},
           {"text": " "},
           {"text": "α]"}]]},
        {"text":
         " together with instances of whatever operations are used in the tactic"},
        {"raw": "\n"},
        {"text": "call."}]]},
     {"element":
      ["p",
       true,
       [],
       [{"text": "The variant "},
        {"element":
         ["code",
          true,
          [],
          [{"text": "linear_combination"},
           {"text": " "},
           {"text": "(norm"},
           {"text": " "},
           {"text": ":="},
           {"text": " "},
           {"text": "tac)"},
           {"text": " "},
           {"text": "e"}]]},
        {"text": " specifies explicitly the \"normalization tactic\""},
        {"raw": "\n"},
        {"element": ["code", true, [], [{"text": "tac"}]]},
        {"text":
         " to be run on the subgoal(s) after constructing the linear combination."}]]},
     {"element":
      ["ul",
       true,
       [],
       [{"element":
         ["li",
          true,
          [],
          [{"text": "The default normalization tactic is "},
           {"element": ["code", true, [], [{"text": "ring1"}]]},
